match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-19 Fiorentina vs Torino
match.strDescriptionEN: Fiorentina takes on Torino in the opening game of the 2020/21 Serie A season. Torino spent the majority of last season fighting for survival in Italy’s top flight and lost 2-0 to Fiorentina when these two teams clashed in July.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-19 Verona vs Roma
match.strDescriptionEN: Hellas Verona takes on Roma in a Serie A clash as the season gets underway. The visitor will have to make do without its promising young midfielder Nicolo Zaniolo, after he tore his ACL for the second time in eight months on international duty.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-20 Genoa vs Crotone
match.strDescriptionEN: Crotone takes on Genoa on its return to the Italian top flight, following its promotion from Serie B last season. The road side will be relying once again on the goals of Simy Nwankwo, who was the second division top scorer with 20 goals.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-20 Juventus vs Sampdoria
match.strDescriptionEN: Juventus gets its Serie A title defence underway against Sampdoria at Allianz Stadium. Italian legend Andrea Pirlo is now the manager of the Old Lady and will be looking to win the club’s tenth successive league title.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-20 Parma Calcio 1913 vs Napoli
match.strDescriptionEN: Napoli begins its Serie A campaign on the road against Parma. This will be Gennaro Gattuso's first full season in charge of Napoli, with the Italian looking to get his team back challenge for UEFA Champions League qualification and the league title.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-20 Sassuolo vs Cagliari
match.strDescriptionEN: Sassuolo and Cagliari kick off their 2020/21 Serie A campaigns against one another at Mapei Stadium. The two have played six Serie A games here in the past, with Cagliari as yet unable to muster a win, including last season's 2-2 draw in December.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-21 Milan vs Bologna
match.strDescriptionEN: AC Milan gets its season underway against Bologna at the San Siro. Milan managed to beat Bologna 3-2 and 5-1 during the 2019/20 campaign which saw the Rossoneri land a UEFA Europa League qualifying spot after a disappointing start.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-30 Benevento vs Inter
Italian Serie A 2020-09-30 Lazio vs Atalanta
match.strDescriptionEN: Two of Serie A’s most entertaining teams go head-to-head as Lazio hosts Atalanta. Ciro Immobile scored a stoppage-time penalty to rescue a dramatic point in this game last season, keeping his cool from 12 yards out to ensure a 3-3 tie.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-30 Udinese vs Spezia
Italian Serie A 2020-09-26 Cagliari vs Lazio
match.strDescriptionEN: Striker Ciro Immobile and his Lazio team are back on the road to take on Cagliari. The host thought it had earned three points when these two met here last season before two extra-time goals from Lazio left Cagliari fans heartbroken.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-26 Inter vs Fiorentina
match.strDescriptionEN: Antonio Conte's Inter Milan starts its Serie A campaign against the visiting Fiorentina. Despite challenging for the title last season Inter was unable to beat Fiorentina, with the purple-clad team battling to secure two draws.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-26 Sampdoria vs Benevento
match.strDescriptionEN: Sampdoria, a side which flirted with relegation last season, takes on newly-promoted Benevento. The away side ran away with Serie B last season, with Filippo Inzaghi's men promoted with ease after winning the league by an impressive 18 points.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-26 Torino vs Atalanta
match.strDescriptionEN: Torino welcomes Atalanta to Turin for its first home game of the 2020/21 Serie A campaign. This fixture was one to forget for Torino last season, as it was reduced to nine men and on the wrong end of a 7-0 Atalanta thrashing.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-27 Crotone vs Milan
match.strDescriptionEN: Simeon Nwankwo scored 20 goals during Crotone's successful promotion route from Serie B last season. He tries to replicate that form in Italy's top-flight, with Crotone's first home match against a rebuilding AC Milan.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-27 Napoli vs Genoa
match.strDescriptionEN: Gennaro Gattuso produced Napoli's first trophy in six years with its Coppa Italia victory last season. Now, the objective is to challenge for the Serie A title, a dream that continues with a match again expected relegation candidate Genoa.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-27 Roma vs Juventus
match.strDescriptionEN: Roma open Stadio Olimpico for the Serie A season with the visit of the champions, Juventus. Diego Perotti came to the forefront with a brace as the Italian capital team defeated the Old Lady 3-1, after having won the league title a week prior.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-27 Spezia vs Sassuolo
match.strResult: A 114-year-old club makes its debut in the Italian top flight as Spezia plays its first-ever game at this level at home against Sassuolo. The host needed to go through the playoffs to get here and faces a tough challenge to avoid Serie A relegation.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-27 Verona vs Udinese
match.strDescriptionEN: Appointment at Bentegodi for Hellas Verona and Udinese: both teams have the minimum goal of salvation for this season, but they know they have the potential to aim even higher. Who will win?

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-09-28 Bologna vs Parma Calcio 1913
match.strDescriptionEN: Bologna hosts Parma in the first Derby dell'Emilia of the campaign. Last season the two teams could not be separated, twice playing out 2-2 draws in the league and also finishing 12th and 11th respectively in the Serie A table.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-02 Fiorentina vs Sampdoria
match.strDescriptionEN: Almost eight months after being dismantled 5-1 at home by Fiorentina, Claudio Ranieri’s Sampdoria travels to Florence aiming to restore its pride. Federico Chiesa scored a brace that day and despite transfer speculation, remains at Fiorentina.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-03 Sassuolo vs Crotone
match.strDescriptionEN: After losing 4-1 at Genoa a fortnight ago in its return to Serie A after a two-year exile, Crotone's second road match of the new campaign comes at Sassuolo. The host won this fixture 2-1 three seasons ago.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-03 Udinese vs Roma
match.strDescriptionEN: Roma left Stadio Friuli last year with a handsome 4-0 victory, courtesy of four different goalscorers. Udinese scored the fewest amount of goals that season but expects Fernando Forestieri’s return to the club will rejuvenate the strike force.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-04 Atalanta vs Cagliari
match.strDescriptionEN: Stadio Atleti Azzurri d'Italia opens for Serie A with Atalanta hosting Cagliari. The visitor from Sardinia finished 11 places below Atalanta in 2019/20 yet managed a 2-0 win in the corresponding game last year with a rare goal from Christian Oliva.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-04 Benevento vs Bologna
match.strDescriptionEN: Four days after hosting Antonio Conte's Inter Milan, Benevento welcomes Bologna to Stadio Ciro Vigorito. Three years ago, a Godfred Donsah goal was enough to earn Bologna a victory in its one and only visit to Benevento.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-04 Juventus vs Napoli
match.strDescriptionEN: Last time Juventus and Napoli played, the Neapolitan side celebrated its first major trophy in six years by winning the Coppa Italia on penalties. Can Andrea Pirlo’s total-football approach exact some revenge for the Old Lady?

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-04 Lazio vs Inter
match.strDescriptionEN: Last season at Stadio Olimpico, Sergej Milinkovic-Savic scored the winner for Lazio in a 2-1 victory against Inter Milan. Simone Inzaghi will want to build on last year’s 4th place finish and can set a precedent against the visitor.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-04 Milan vs Spezia
match.strDescriptionEN: Two weeks after opening its Serie A campaign with a 2-0 home victory - largely thanks to a Zlatan Ibrahimovic brace - AC Milan returns home as Spezia visits San Siro in the league for the first time in history.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-04 Parma Calcio 1913 vs Verona
match.strDescriptionEN: After both being promoted in recent seasons, Parma and Hellas Verona are now seeking to consolidate their Serie A status. They meet in an early-season encounter at Stadio Ennio Tardini, where a Darko Lazovic goal earned Hellas a 1-0 win last year.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-11-04 Genoa vs Torino
Italian Serie A 2020-10-17 Crotone vs Juventus
match.strDescriptionEN: Serie A newcomer Crotone hosts champion Juventus at Stadio Ezio Scida, having lost its opening three league games so far this season. The Pitagorici did however earn a creditable 1-1 draw when Juventus last visited the ground two years ago.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-17 Inter vs Milan
match.strDescriptionEN: The fabled Derby della Madonnina - contested by Inter Milan and AC Milan - has divided households in Italy and beyond for almost a century. Inter supporters have enjoyed it in recent years, with the Nerazzurri winning the teams’ last four matchups.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-17 Napoli vs Atalanta
match.strDescriptionEN: Serie A returns after the international break as Napoli hosts Atalanta. Napoli was unable to fulfil its game with Juventus last time out, with the defending Serie A champion being handed a 3-0 victory and Napoli hit with a one-point deduction.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-17 Sampdoria vs Lazio
match.strDescriptionEN: Claudio Ranieri’s Sampdoria welcomes Lazio to Luigi Ferraris Stadium. Lazio completed a league double over Sampdoria last season, with Ciro Immobile netting a hat-trick in a 5-1 win at Rome's Stadio Olimpico.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-18 Bologna vs Sassuolo
match.strDescriptionEN: Sassuolo looks to continue its fairy-tale start to the season when as it travels to Bologna. Currently third 3rd in the table and undefeated, the Neroverdi come into this game on the back of two consecutive 4-1 victories.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-18 Roma vs Benevento
match.strDescriptionEN: Serie B champion Benevento heads to Stadio Olimpico to face Roma. The Giallorossi will want to build on the 1-0 win against Udinese before the break. The corresponding fixture two seasons ago saw a seven-goal thriller, finishing 5-2 to the home side.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-18 Spezia vs Fiorentina
match.strDescriptionEN: Newly-promoted Spezia takes on Serie A stalwart Fiorentina, in what is the home side's fourth ever game in the Italian top flight. It's been a mixed bag for Vincenzo Italiano's men so far, with a fantastic 2-0 win over Udinese the highlight.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-18 Torino vs Cagliari
match.strDescriptionEN: Torino hosts Cagliari at Stadio Olimpico as both teams look to secure a first win of the season. The fixture last season finished in a 1-1 draw, with Cagliari winning the corresponding meeting 4-2, which included a goal for Radja Nainggolan.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-18 Udinese vs Parma Calcio 1913
match.strDescriptionEN: Still yet to win a game this season, Udinese hosts Parma. The 2020/21 campaign has been one to forget so far for Udinese, losing its opening three matches, and is now coming up against a Parma team which it lost to twice last season.

match.strFilename: Italian Serie A 2020-10-19 Verona vs Genoa
match.strDescriptionEN: Hellas Verona, which opened the season with a magnificent 3-0 victory over Roma, takes on Genoa at Luigi Ferraris Stadium. Rolando Maran’s side however, went into the break with a demoralizing 6-0 loss at Napoli.
